<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>ADIF MCP — LoTW Adapter</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header class="card">
      <div class="site-title">
        <span class="badge">ADIF MCP</span> LoTW Adapter
      </div>
      <nav class="topnav">
        <a href="https://adif-mcp.com">Core</a>
        <a href="https://lotw.adif-mcp.com">LoTW Adapter</a>
        <a href="https://eqsl.adif-mcp.com">eQSL Adapter</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/KI7MT/adif-mcp-lotw">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="card">
        <h1>LoTW Adapter</h1>
        <p>
          <strong>adif-mcp-lotw</strong> bridges the ADIF MCP core with
          <a href="https://lotw.arrl.org/lotwhelp">Logbook of The World (LoTW)</a>.
          It provides safe MCP tools for fetching confirmations, award statuses, and future uploads.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Fetch QSO confirmations via LoTW API</li>
          <li>Query award/endorsement status</li>
          <li>Normalize LoTW fields into canonical ADIF schema</li>
          <li>Agent-friendly JSON responses</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card">
        <h2>Roadmap</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>M1 — Read-only confirmations</li>
          <li>M2 — Awards status integration</li>
          <li>M3 — Upload support (optional)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
      © 2025 ADIF MCP Project · MIT License
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>

</html>
